rComments: Very boring lectures, all the information is read off the slides and are word for word copied from the textbook. This makes going to class pointless,but random attendance is taken. Group work is required through the whole term and is worth 45%. This is too much of your mark to be relying on other people to produce quality work. Would not recommend.

She is nice, but her lectures are boring and pointless. She basically just reads out loud everything that's on her lecture slides. With that being said, her slides are quite informative. Make sure you understand her diagrams/graphics and are able to recognize what they represent.  She'll put some of them on the midterm and exam.

Good class. Lecture material is long but was most important for the test and exam. Straightforward in a sense that your knowledge of the lectures will show in your grade. Pretty fair and I would recommend this as a SCI credit for geography majors in the arts.

Can be really helpful. However her English is not fluent. Her midterms and exams are the same format as Professor Conway's papers. Overall the course itself is interesting. She is definitely more interesting than Conway.
